            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1674558544337-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required) to the pan and cook for an initial 2-3 min</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394753719-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394753719-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394753719-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394753719-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394753719-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion petals</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the pork is starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702394764398-x200.jpg",
