    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork mince is starting to brown, add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Be careful – the garlic and ginger will sizzle from the heat of the oil</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Vietnamese-style pork</strong></p>",
